      • startWindow

        public void startWindow(int window,
                        java.lang.Object obj,
                        int index)
        Starts a certain window based off of the given index
        Parameters:
        i - Selection of which window to start 0 - Login Window 1 - Admin Window 2 - Albums Window 3 - Photos Window 4 - SlideShow Window This method should not be called by passing in an actual integer, it should only be called by the Controller classes using the final values listed in this class in order to change the window.

      • setCurrUser

        public void setCurrUser(User currUser)
        Sets the user that is currently logged into the application. This should be set only when a user logs in through the log in page, so the only place this method should be called with an actual username is in the LoginController. In any window, when a user logs out, the current user should be set to null.
        Parameters:
        currUser -
